        'The 5 Rs for saving the environment are:\n\n1. Refuse — Say "no" to things you do not need or to things that harm the environment. For example, refuse a plastic carry bag when you don\'t need one.\n\n2. Reduce — Change your habits and use less of everything to generate less waste. For example, take only as much food as you will eat.\n\n3. Reuse — Use what you buy many times instead of throwing it away after one use. For example, use a cloth bag for shopping every day.\n\n4. Repurpose — Put an old item to a completely new and different use. For example, use an old newspaper to wrap books or cover shelves, or use old jars as pen stands.\n\n5. Recycle — Use waste material to make a brand new product. For example, old newspapers are sent to recycling factories where they are turned into new paper.',
